{"$ambrosia":"aero:interactive:9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8:*","$id":"01a447e0-44e0-11ed-801f-949c2765923b","$workspaceId":"7fff47c0-44d6-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","$projectId":"86cb0040-44df-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca","annotations":[],"configSchemaVersion":"/pluginGenericSchema/v1","config":{"stage":{"sections":[{"rowsAreFullWidth":false,"backgroundImageUrl":"","rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"03eced5d-018d-49ce-a14b-5863ec2df7b1","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Information, Competition, and Stock Prices","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"a4566e9e-7e72-42eb-a89b-d9bdcac40a63"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"1","startValue":22},"ref":"2ce85a68-47c6-480f-917b-66314ae7fb4b","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"d096b621-4c11-4a06-874a-f0ec39062a9a","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"9ab5946d-cc31-4e3c-b9d6-20d96e74ff84","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Summit Systems has an equity cost of capital of 11%, will pay a dividend of $1.50 in one year and its dividends had been expected to grow by 6% per year. You read in the paper that Summit has revised its growth prospects and now expects its dividends to grow at a rate of 3% per year forever.","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"8f0dc34c-e208-4301-9346-04b7ee3b0701","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"4346a24a-a712-48fb-aee7-edb60bcf0339","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"cd6ce59d-0a18-452b-8940-791634ae771c","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What is the drop in the value of a share of Summit Systems stock based on this information?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"54fcab6f-2582-47ee-ad01-b688c7ca6f42","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"4420e6be-9b16-4d36-99da-677baedc1c6d","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"If you tried to sell your Summit Systems stock after reading this news, what price would you be likely to get? Why?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"be00ca4f-65c1-42d4-a4d8-c3cc0825f0f5","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"e9034db8-080e-464c-aea5-13900a7df15e","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Assume that Cola Co. has a share price of $43. The firm will pay a dividend of $1.24 in one year, and you expect Cola Co. to raise this dividend by approximately 7% per year in perpetuity.","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"2efc941d-47a8-42a8-b159-13d2f044791f","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"0aa3f222-f366-4f4e-8761-75299b157e12","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"3a0d19f7-c7cc-4f8b-b571-582fbc3a55a6","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"If Cola Co.’s equity cost of capital is 8%, what share price would you expect based on your estimate of the dividend growth rate?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"778d8f60-1ef4-410b-a2c4-f3d30f1a4b26","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"db3b076d-29cf-4e4f-a1e6-9851e2199f6d","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Given Cola Co.’s share price, what would you conclude about your assessment of Cola Co.’s future dividend growth?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"1f5a446c-c42c-4b1b-9cd5-8c139bd8e728","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"863ca2d4-4fb0-4713-aff1-752944aa5021","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Roybus, Inc., a manufacturer of flash memory, just reported that its main production facility in Taiwan was destroyed in a fire. Although the plant was fully insured, the loss of production will decrease Roybus’s free cash flow by $180 million at the end of this year and by $60 million at the end of next year.","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"0ece24a3-5664-4785-a7a1-73b4156ee5d3","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"a06970e5-f6f9-475f-ad82-f5cb67faf935","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"efc92665-328f-4aa5-aa65-025c51b35aa3","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"If Roybus has 35 million shares outstanding and a weighted average cost of capital of 13%, what change in Roybus’s stock price would you expect upon this announcement? (Assume the value of Roybus’s debt is not affected by the event.)","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"022e8368-bb90-4a11-acfd-902a5a4c5f59","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"ebc04b0b-be23-4618-8056-7e0cf166c0ec","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Would you expect to be able to sell Roybus stock on hearing this announcement and make a profit? Explain.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"26d87a60-c0a6-4a17-a787-837f6b1d6d02","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"120c59dc-ad14-4182-b5a5-cc1d050b34ef","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Apnex, Inc., is a biotechnology firm that is about to announce the results of its clinical trials of a potential new cancer drug. If the trials were successful, Apnex stock will be worth $70 per share. If the trials were unsuccessful, Apnex stock will be worth $18 per share. Suppose that the morning before the announcement is scheduled, Apnex shares are trading for $55 per share.","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"795f0c17-150b-42eb-9b76-ddbd6c9b300f","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"e9e0b829-f968-4b29-8883-990552793102","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"d31ea4c7-ef1a-4dc7-bb2d-025fc265b314","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Based on the current share price, what sort of expectations do investors seem to have about the success of the trials?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"6a2ccf85-d64d-49cf-93a4-0606a84fc385","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"77cfa066-6556-4da6-b69c-9c05c3e14f80","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Suppose hedge fund manager Paul Kliner has hired several prominent research scientists to examine the public data on the drug and make their own assessment of the drug’s promise. Would Kliner’s fund be likely to profit by trading the stock in the hours prior to the announcement?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"cce0d16b-de39-44ac-ba61-a29ee92ae1cd","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"045dab6f-5c1a-4ee4-ba67-a37d0896a620","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Which factors would limit the ability of Kliner’s fund to profit on its information?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"e9099fe3-0050-4498-98c4-cd50414daeb3"}]}]}]}]},"screenType":"","transitions":{"enter":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""},"exit":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""}},"lockElements":false,"learnerCurrentAttempt":1,"footer":{"buttonText":"Next","buttonIcon":"Arrow","showFooter":false,"showHistoryNavButtons":false,"previewFooter":false,"position":"Fixed to screen bottom","footerComponent":{"showFooterDropArea":"hide","width":100,"footerComponentsAlignment":"right"}},"styles":{"background":{},"stage":{"maxWidth":940,"background":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","responsive":true,"padding":{"vertical":60,"horizontal":60},"border":{"color":"rgba(224, 224, 224, 1)","radius":0,"width":0}},"elements":{"padding":{"vertical":10,"horizontal":10}},"footer":{"buttonColor":"rgba(0, 115, 202, 1)","textColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)","backgroundColor":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","padding":10,"corners":4,"border":"none","shadow":"0 -1px 4px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.06), 0 0 12px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1)"},"feedback":{"width":320,"textColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)","backgroundColor":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","corners":4,"border":"none","shadow":"0 5px 47px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.15), 0 10px 20px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1), 0 7px 8px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.1)"}},"title":"Information, Competition, and Stock Prices"},"assets":[],"scenarios":[],"pluginPayload":{"pluginRepositoryPath":"https://plugin-repository-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8/0.15.209/ac43ee4c0eda05e9718fa83a5aed4cff.zip","summary":{"pluginId":"9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8","name":"Screen","description":"A screen of a lesson","type":"screen","latestVersion":"0.15.209","subscriptionId":"f0afd4d0-d2ff-11ea-9998-d57e1e28aca1","createdAt":"Fri, 6 Mar 2020 04:11:39 GMT","updatedAt":"Tue, 13 Dec 2022 22:07:46 GMT","tags":[],"publishMode":"DEFAULT"}},"activityThemeIconLibraries":[]}